get.description:
List forecasts.

**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `workforce_management:read:admin`

**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `workforce_management:read:forecasts:admin`

**[Rate Limit Label](https://marketplace.zoom.us/docs/api-reference/rate-limits#rate-limits):** `MEDIUM`

**Not supported in Gov cluster**

parameters.name: next_page_token
parameters.description: The next page token from the previous page, if available. Not required for the first page.

parameters.name: page_size
parameters.description: The number of items to be returned per page.

next_page_token.description: Use the next page token to paginate through large result sets. A next page token will be returned whenever the set of available results exceeds the current page size.

page_size.description: The number of items returned per page.

total_records.description: The total number of items available across all pages.

interval_minutes.description: The forecast granularity length, in minutes.

scheduling_groups.description: List of scheduling groups present in the forecast.

anyOf.description: Null if color code is not present.

sla.description: Service level target goal percentage. `-1` if not set.

sla_target_time.description: Service level target time in seconds. `-1` if not set.

asa.description: Average speed of answer in seconds. `-1` if not set.

fixed_shrinkage.description: Fixed shrinkage value to use for all days.

anyOf.description: Value will be `null` if `dynamic_shrinkage` is present.

dynamic_shrinkage.description: Dynamic shrinkage value to use, based on configured days.

dynamic_config.description: List of shrinkage values for required intervals.

days.description: List of days this configuration will apply for.

items.description:
`0` - Sunday 
`1` - Monday
`2` - Tuesday
`3` - Wednesday
`4` - Thursday
`5` - Friday
`6` - Saturday

start_time.description: The starting minute of a day to apply this shrinkage value.

end_time.description: The ending minute of a day until when to apply this shrinkage value.

anyOf.description: Value will be `null` if `fixed_shrinkage` is present.

deferrable_sla.description: Deferrable channels interactions' percentage. `-1` if not set.

deferrable_sla_target_time.description: Deferrable channels interactions' target time in hours. `-1` if not set.

429.description:
**HTTP Status Code:** `429`
Too Many Requests. For more information, see [rate limits](/docs/api/rest/rate-limits/).

post.description:
Import historical queue metrics to Workforce Management (WFM).

**[Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `workforce_management:write:admin`

**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `workforce_management:write:queue_metrics:admin`

**[Rate Limit Label](https://marketplace.zoom.us/docs/api-reference/rate-limits#rate-limits):** `HEAVY`

**Not supported in Gov cluster**

file.description: Attachment file. Only CSV format is supported. For format details, log in to WFM and visit **Forecasting -> Historical data -> Import historical data**.

timezone.description: The timezone of the intervals in the CSV file. The default is `UTC`.

allow_overwrite.description: When set to `false`, the import fails if existing data conflicts with the uploaded data.

get.description:
List all the schedule agents for the particular date and timezone

**[Granular Scopes](https://developers.zoom.us/docs/integrations/oauth-scopes-overview/):** `workforce_management:read:list_schedule_agents:admin`

**[Rate Limit Label](https://marketplace.zoom.us/docs/api-reference/rate-limits#rate-limits):** `MEDIUM`

parameters.name: user_ids
parameters.description: Return results only for the specified user IDs. Add multiple `user_ids` parameters to include more users. Example: `?user_ids=123&user_ids=456`.

parameters.name: timezone
parameters.description: The schedule's timezone. The default is UTC.

parameters.name: next_page_token
parameters.description: Use the next page token to paginate through large result sets. A next page token returns whenever the set of available results exceeds the current page size.

parameters.name: page_size
parameters.description: The number of scheduled agents returned per page.

200.description: List of agents in the schedule for the date

next_page_token.description: Use the next page token to paginate through large result sets. A next page token returns whenever the set of available results exceeds the current page size.

page_size.description: The number of scheduled agents returned per page.

total_records.description: The total number of all scheduled agents available across pages.

timezone.description: The schedule's timezone. The default is UTC.

agents.description: List of agents in the schedule

scheduling_group_name.description: The name of the scheduling group

total_scheduled_time.description: The total schedule duration, in minutes.

total_paid_time.description: The total duration of paid schedule activity in minutes

start_time.description: The schedule activity start time. In ISO 8601 format (yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss'Z' or yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssTZD).

end_time.description: The schedule activity end time. in ISO 8601 format (yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss'Z' or yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssTZD).

is_paid.description: The is_paid indicates if the scheduled activity counts as paid time for calculating the agent's total paid duration.
